      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ $json.body.data.reply.text_body }}",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are an expert email reply classifier specializing in roundtable event invitations.\n\nAnalyze the email reply and return ONLY this exact format, nothing else:\n\nclassification: [Positive/False Positive/Negative]\nactual_reply: [extracted reply text]\nreasoning: [one sentence]\nred_flags: [concerns or None]\n\nCLASSIFICATION RULES:\n- Positive: Genuine interest, confirmed attendance, or asking for more details before committing\n- False Positive: Seems positive but sarcastic, contradictory, or confused about their role (e.g. asking about speaking fees, \"sure but I won't show up\")\n- Negative: Clear rejection, unsubscribe request, or out-of-office with no actual reply\n\nEXTRACTING ACTUAL REPLY \u2014 strip out everything below, keep only the prospect's words:\n- Email signatures (name, title, phone, address, company)\n- Quoted thread (everything after \"-----Original Message-----\" or \"On [date]... wrote:\")\n- Lines starting with \">\"\n- Unsubscribe links\n- \"Sent from my iPhone/Outlook\" footers"
        }
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3,
      "position": [
        640,
        0
      ],
      "id": "a1e17807-58e7-4a83-9d03-d8d903c5a1ec",
